Intentional Self-Harm Mortality

It’s a world wide suicide

Zackary Scalyer

April 28, 2019

Input data

Google BigQuery with kaggle.com Python type kernel

  • World Bank: Education Data

This dataset combines key education statistics from a variety of sources to provide a look at global literacy, spending, and access

  • World Development Indicators (WDI)

World Development Indicators Data is the primary World Bank collection of development indicators, compiled from officially-recognized international sources. It presents the most current and accurate global development data available, and includes national, regional and global estimates.

20 potential regressors where selected by indicator name, code, and value; 10 from World Bank Eduction and 10 from World Development Indicators.

World Health Organization (WHO) Mortality Database

  • Selected potential regressor, sucide counts, and exported data table with online tool.

    ‘No. of deaths - Intentional self-harm’, for all countries from 1999 to 2016

Global Health Observatory data repository

  • Download complete data sets for each measure of sucide rate.

    ‘Suicide mortality rate (per 100 000 population)’. Number of suicide deaths in a year, divided by the population and multiplied by 100 000.

    ‘Age-standardized mortality rate (per 100 000 population)’. The age-standardized mortality rate is a weighted average of the age-specific mortality rates per 100 000 persons, where the weights are the proportions of persons in the corresponding age groups of the WHO standard population.

    • Observed units of country by sex for 2016, 2015, 2010, 2005, and 2000.

World Health Statistics data visualizations dashboard

  • Download complete data set containing suicide rate and a measure of non-self-harm related mortality.

    ‘Probability of dying between exact ages 30 and 70 from any of cardiovascular disease, cancer, diabetes, or chronic respiratory disease.’. Percent of 30-year-old-people who would die before their 70th birthday from any of cardiovascular disease, cancer, diabetes, or chronic respiratory disease, assuming that s/he would experience current mortality rates at every age and s/he would not die from any other cause of death (e.g., injuries or HIV/AIDS).

    ‘Suicide mortality rate (per 100 000 population)’. Number of suicide deaths in a year, divided by the population and multiplied by 100 000.

    • Observed units of country by sex for 2016, 2015, 2010, 2005, and 2000.

# fun for listing contrys' that mached|unmached to a region in worldMap 
checkingCountry <- function(full_dat, worldMap){
  require(dplyr)
  return(list(
    nomatch = unique(full_dat$country[!(full_dat$country %in% unique(worldMap$region))]) %>%
               sort() %>% 
               as.character(),
    match = unique(full_dat$country[(full_dat$country %in% unique(worldMap$region))]) %>%
               sort() %>% 
               as.character()
    )
  )
}


## functions to help fit models with clean data in a genaric way
# given a data set, select only varables for a model
z.getModelDat <- function(dat, DV, IVs){
  return(dat %>% select(append(DV,IVs)) %>% drop_na()) 
}

# fit a model given data, responce as char, and regressiors as chars
z.getFit <- function(dat, DV, IVs, wts = NULL){
  return(dat %>% 
           select(append(DV,IVs)) %>% 
           drop_na() %>% 
           lm(as.formula(paste(DV, '~', 
                               paste0(IVs, collapse = '+'))),
              data = .,
              weights = wts)
         )
}

# function for nested stepwise model building  
z.step <- function(dat,
                   DV = 'suicide_rate',
                   IVs = c("growth", "preprimary", "UnemployMale", "GDP", "dying")){
  mod_dat <- z.getModelDat(dat, DV, IVs)
  fit.null <- lm(as.formula(paste(DV, '~', '1')), data = mod_dat)
  fit.full <- lm(as.formula(paste(DV, '~', paste0(IVs, collapse = '+'))),
                 data = mod_dat)
  return(step(fit.null,
              scope = list(lower = fit.null, upper = fit.full),
              direction = c('forward')))
}

# function for ploting model coeffents with broom::tidy() resutls of fit    
z.plotMargin_results <- function(fit_results, title = 'Marginal Coeffents'){
  return(fit_results %>%
           filter(term != '(Intercept)') %>% 
           ggplot(., aes(x = term, y = estimate, color = term)) +
           geom_hline(yintercept = 0, color = "sienna", linetype="dashed") +
#           geom_point(aes(size=abs(statistic))) +
           geom_point() +
           geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = conf.low, ymax = conf.high), width = 0.2) +
           scale_color_discrete(guide=FALSE) +
           labs(title = title, x = NULL)  +
           theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
           coord_flip()
         )
}

# functions for fitting weights
# varance method
wts.varfun <- function(fit){
  return(1/fitted(lm(residuals(fit)^2 ~ fitted(fit))))
}

# standrd deveation method
wts.sdfun <- function(fit){
  if (!any(fitted(lm(abs(residuals(fit)) ~ fitted(fit))) < 0)){
    return(1/fitted(lm(abs(residuals(fit)) ~ fitted(fit)))^2)
  } else{
    return(print('at least one wt < 0'))
  }
}

# puts both together
wtsfun <- function(fit){
  if (!any(wts.varfun(fit) < 0)){
    return(wts.varfun(fit))
  } else if (!any(fitted(lm(abs(residuals(fit)) ~ fitted(fit))) < 0)){
    return(wts.sdfun(fit))
  } else{
    return(print('weights can not be negitive'))
  }
}

# Nested data by year with abreveated names
selfharm_nest <- selfharm_dat  %>%
  select(-c(population_total_edu, suicide_per100k,
            suicide_ageadj, suicide_count, precipitation)) %>%
  rename(pop = population_totl_WID, spend = edu_spend_percent, growth = pop_growth_percent,
         netUsers = internet_user_per100, preprimary = teachers_preprimary,
         secondary = teachers_secondary, primary = teachers_primary,
         enrol = enrolment_secondary, female = pop_female_total, male = pop_male_total,
         density = pop_density,  cell = cellular_per100, air = air_transport,
         Unemployment = Unemployment_percent_laborforce, UnemployMale = Unemployment_percent_male,
         UnemployFemale = Unemployment_percent_female, dying = Probability_30to70_dying) %>%
  filter(!is.na(suicide_rate), year != 2016) %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  nest()

# Nested stepwise model fitting  
DV = 'suicide_rate'
# IVs = c('spend', 'growth', 'netUsers', 'preprimary', 'secondary', 'primary',
#         'enrol', 'female', 'male', 'density', 'tourism', 'cell', 'air', 'pop',
#         'Unemployment', 'UnemployMale', 'UnemployFemale', 'GDP', 'dying', 'suicide_rate')
# edu_IVs = c('spend', 'preprimary', 'secondary', 'primary', 'enrol')
IVs = c('growth', 'netUsers', 'female', 'male', 'density', 'tourism', 'cell', 'air', 'pop',
        'Unemployment', 'UnemployMale', 'UnemployFemale', 'GDP', 'dying')



nested_fit_1 <- selfharm_nest %>%
  mutate(model = purrr::map(data, ~ z.step(dat = ., DV = DV, IVs = IVs)),
         results = purrr::map(model, ~ broom::tidy(x = ., conf.int = TRUE, conf.level = 0.95)),
         diagnostics = purrr::map(model, glance))

        'enrol', 'female', 'male', 'density', 'tourism', 'cell', 'air', 'pop',
        'Unemployment', 'UnemployMale', 'UnemployFemale', 'GDP', 'dying')

  mutate(model = purrr::map(data, ~ z.step(dat = ., DV = DV, IVs = IVs)),
         results = purrr::map(model, ~ broom::tidy(x = ., conf.int = TRUE, conf.level = 0.95)),
         diagnostics = purrr::map(model, glance))

# Nested data by year with abreveated names
count_nest <- selfharm_dat  %>%
  select(-c(population_total_edu, suicide_per100k,
            suicide_ageadj, suicide_rate, precipitation)) %>%
  mutate(selfharm_rate = (suicide_count/population_totl_WID)*100000) %>% 
  rename(pop = population_totl_WID, spend = edu_spend_percent, growth = pop_growth_percent,
         netUsers = internet_user_per100, preprimary = teachers_preprimary,
         secondary = teachers_secondary, primary = teachers_primary,
         enrol = enrolment_secondary, female = pop_female_total, male = pop_male_total,
         density = pop_density,  cell = cellular_per100, air = air_transport,
         Unemployment = Unemployment_percent_laborforce, UnemployMale = Unemployment_percent_male,
         UnemployFemale = Unemployment_percent_female, dying = Probability_30to70_dying) %>%
  filter(!is.na(suicide_count)) %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  nest()

# Nested stepwise model fitting  
DV = 'selfharm_rate'
# IVs = c('spend', 'growth', 'netUsers', 'preprimary', 'secondary', 'primary',
#         'enrol', 'female', 'male', 'density', 'tourism', 'cell', 'air', 'pop',
#         'Unemployment', 'UnemployMale', 'UnemployFemale', 'GDP', 'dying', 'suicide_rate')
IVs = c('growth', 'netUsers', 'female', 'male', 'density', 'tourism', 'cell', 'air', 'pop',
        'Unemployment', 'UnemployMale', 'UnemployFemale', 'GDP', 'dying')

# edu_IVs = c('spend', 'preprimary', 'secondary', 'primary', 'enrol')

nestedFit_countRate <- count_nest %>%
  mutate(model = purrr::map(data, ~ z.step(dat = ., DV = DV, IVs = IVs)),
         results = purrr::map(model, ~ broom::tidy(x = ., conf.int = TRUE, conf.level = 0.95)),
         diagnostics = purrr::map(model, glance))

        'enrol', 'female', 'male', 'density', 'tourism', 'cell', 'air', 'pop',
        'Unemployment', 'UnemployMale', 'UnemployFemale', 'GDP', 'dying')

  mutate(model = purrr::map(data, ~ z.step(dat = ., DV = DV, IVs = IVs)),
         results = purrr::map(model, ~ broom::tidy(x = ., conf.int = TRUE, conf.level = 0.95)),
         diagnostics = purrr::map(model, glance))
